comments.body:
@Honny1: I'm not positive that this is not a Podman BUG ...

If you can, based on the Files I provided in **this Issue**, provide a COMPLETE Example (so we are using the same Configuration Parameters) that you can confirm works correctly on your End (using either `HealthCmd` or `Systemd Restart`).

I never had `Restart=always` within a Pod, but alright, adding it wasn't an Issue. The Issue is that even with that Addition it won't work as expected 😕.

@Honny1 I see that this specific line is still from the original implementation of supporting `.pod` units. IIRC, I was trying to mimic the output of the `podman generate systemd` command and I guess I just copied it from there.

I also see that the command itself was changed since to not override the `Environment` field. So, as always, we need to fix issues as users use different parts of the code :).
I think the way to address this is to check if the user has set a value. If not, set `Restart=on-failure` to maintain backward compatibility and if yes, leave as it.
